  <article>
    <h1>My Story</h1>
    <p>As an active classical guitarist, I developed task-specific focal hand dystonia, which caused my right-hand index finger to clench involuntarily into my palm whenever I attempted to play. Like many, I was met with discouraging prognoses from medical specialists who declared there was no cure.</p>
    
    <p>Refusing to accept a lifetime of not playing, I began researching motor learning, neuroplasticity, and biomechanics. Through trial, error, and meticulous observation of hand ergonomics, I designed a custom retraining protocol that successfully resolved my symptoms, allowing me to play and teach again.</p>

    <blockquote>
      "By understanding that the brain has simply mismapped the movements, we can use targeted physical constraints and exercises to teach it the correct paths once more."
    </blockquote>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/about/my-approach" class="btn">Learn About My Approach &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </article>
